### Concurrent-worker caveat

While this worker was still running, the outbound worker pushed `94a78ce2` and
included `packages/message-contract/src/index.ts` plus the inbound schema test,
both of which import `../inbound-events`. The actual
`packages/message-contract/inbound-events.ts` remains intentionally uncommitted
under this task's no-commit rule. Therefore `origin/main` is temporarily
incomplete until steering commits the inbound slice (or removes those two
cross-slice imports). Do not mistake the local green checks for a fresh-clone
receipt until that integration lands.


## Steering close — 2026-07-16

Live-proven and closed: six taps wired at the worker's verified
insertion points behind CHAT_SDK_INBOUND_SHADOW_ENABLED=1; first real
shadow events landed at 21:23Z from Joel's own Telegram button tap —
`message/inbound.interaction` (actor joel, isBot false, canExecute
false, sdk vercel/chat@4.34.0, lineage id) + `message/inbound.diff`
whose FIRST report already caught a conversationId semantic mismatch
between legacy and SDK. Fail-open proven live too: the initial Slack
tap construct failure (unexported token) never touched legacy traffic.
